  "text": "The canonical patterns for deploying services in Kubernetes are documented across multiple repositories:\n\n1. **API Type Definition (Authoritative)**: The definitive `Deployment` struct is defined in the API specification repository at `github.com/sg-evals/api--v0.32.0/apps/v1/types.go` (lines 359-372). This struct includes TypeMeta and ObjectMeta for Kubernetes metadata management, a DeploymentSpec for desired state, and a DeploymentStatus for the observed state. The DeploymentSpec (lines 375-418) contains critical fields including Replicas (desired pod count), Selector (label selector for managing pods), Template (PodTemplateSpec for pod configuration), Strategy (deployment strategy like RollingUpdate), and ProgressDeadlineSeconds.\n\n2. **Internal API Type**: The Kubernetes internal unversioned API maintains a parallel definition at `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0/pkg/apis/apps/types.go` (lines 352-416) which mirrors the external v1 API structure but with less strict typing in some fields. This allows the cluster to manage conversions between API versions.\n\n3. **Versioned API in Kubernetes Staging**: A duplicate external API is maintained in the kubernetes repository at `github.com/sg-evals/kubernetes--v1.32.0/staging/src/k8s.io/api/apps/v1/types.go` for staging and distribution purposes.\n\n4. **Client-Side Code Pattern (Typed Client)**: The canonical Go client example is located at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go`. This demonstrates the standard workflow: (1) Building a kubeconfig-based client configuration via `clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags()`, (2) Creating a Clientset via `kubernetes.NewForConfig()`, (3) Getting a typed deployments client via `clientset.AppsV1().Deployments(namespace)`, (4) Constructing a Deployment object with ObjectMeta and DeploymentSpec, and (5) Creating, updating, and deleting the resource via the client methods. The example shows proper pod template configuration with labels, selectors, and container specs.\n\n5. **Dynamic Client Pattern**: An alternative approach using the dynamic client is documented at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/examples/dynamic-create-update-delete-deployment/main.go`, which uses unstructured data for more flexibility at runtime.\n\n6. **Developer Documentation**: The primary README is at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md`, which provides step-by-step instructions for compiling and running the example, explains the Create/Update/Delete workflow, and includes a retry pattern for handling conflicts during updates. The examples directory overview at `github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0/examples/README.md` provides context for other example patterns and links to relevant documentation.\n\nThe key architectural pattern is that the API types are defined in the api repository (for distribution), mirrored in the kubernetes repository (for internal use), and consumed by client-go through type-safe client sets that provide methods for Create, Get, Update, Delete, and List operations on Kubernetes resources."
}

